### EHS Reporting Portal — sample API calls
#
# A ready-to-run walk-through of the full capture flow, in order:
#   identify -> create -> save details -> load template -> save checklist -> submit
#
# How to use:
#   - VS Code: install the "REST Client" extension, then click "Send Request"
#     above each block.
#   - JetBrains IDEs: open this file and use the inline "Run" gutter icon.
#   - The @reportId variable is captured from the create response, so run the
#     requests top to bottom.
#
# The backend listens on http://localhost:8080 (no auth). Start it with
# `mvn spring-boot:run` from backend/ — see README.md.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Identify — is there a resumable draft for this person?
# Returns { resume: false } for a new reporter, or { resume: true, report, mismatchWarning? }.
POST {{host}}/api/identify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Asha Rao",
  "employeeId": "E1024",
  "designation": "Line Operator"
}

### 2. Create a new report (Step-0). Captures the id used by every later call.
# @name createReport
POST {{host}}/api/reports
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Asha Rao",
  "employeeId": "E1024",
  "designation": "Line Operator"
}

@reportId = {{createReport.response.body.id}}

### 3. Save Step-1 details (partial or complete; same payload backs Save and Next).
PUT {{host}}/api/reports/{{reportId}}/details
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reportType": "NEAR_MISS",
  "shift": "A",
  "reporterCategory": "STAFF",
  "severity": "MEDIUM",
  "location": "Packing Bay 3",
  "eventDate": "2026-07-17",
  "eventTime": "14:30",
  "reportDescription": "Pallet stacked above the safe height near the walkway.",
  "correctiveAction": "Restacked to safe height; briefed the team.",
  "hodComments": "Verified on shift.",
  "reporterName": "Asha Rao"
}

### 4. Fetch the canonical checklist template (sections + items, in display order).
GET {{host}}/api/checklist-template

### 5. Save Step-2 checklist answers (YES / NO / null to clear). Unknown codes are ignored.
PUT {{host}}/api/reports/{{reportId}}/checklist
Content-Type: application/json

[
  { "itemCode": "PPE_01", "answer": "YES" },
  { "itemCode": "PPE_02", "answer": "NO" },
  { "itemCode": "BEH_01", "answer": "YES" },
  { "itemCode": "TOOL_01", "answer": null }
]

### 6. Submit the report (DRAFT -> SUBMITTED). Re-submitting returns 409 Conflict.
POST {{host}}/api/reports/{{reportId}}/submit

### 7. Read the report back (any time) to inspect saved state.
GET {{host}}/api/reports/{{reportId}}
